Q1: * Original title and title looks the same so I would remove one of the column. I dont think I need homepage, overview and tagline so I would remove these columns. I would put all the title to lower case. I would remove all NAs. I would use clean_names function from janitor.

there seems to be a lot of NAs in the homepage and tagline columns there are two columns: original_title and title that seem to contain similar things theres a lot of movies with a budget and revenue of 0 - presumably missing data youd lose 3310 out of 4803 rows if you dropped all NAs - thats a bit much, so probably better to deal with them in some other way

movies_selected <- movies %>%

movies_runtime <- movies_selected %>%
  mutate(runtime = na_if(runtime, 0))  %>% 
  summarise(count = sum(is.na(runtime)))

Impute the missing values in runtime with the median runtime using coalesce and save this into a new variable called movies_imputed. There should now be no missing values in the column runtime - check this to make sure.

movies_imputed <- movies_runtime %>% 
  mutate(runtime = coalesce(runtime, median(runtime, na.rm = TRUE)))

movies_imputed
sum(is.na(movies_imputed))
[1] 0
longest_runtime <- movies_imputed %>% 
  slice_max(runtime, n = 10)

longest_runtime
shortest_runtime <- movies_imputed %>% 
  slice_min(runtime, n = 10)

shortest_runtime
md <- median(movies_imputed$budget)
movies_imputed <- movies_imputed %>% 
  mutate(budget = 
           if_else(budget < 100, md, budget))

new_budget

movie_budgets <- movies_imputed %>%

    budget_type = case_when(
      budget < 12e6 ~ "Small budget",
      budget < 40e6 ~ "Medium budget",
      budget >= 40e6 ~ "Big budget"
